node.text:
Most people will tell you why you can’t or shouldn’t do it.  They’ll elaborate to you or behind your back that your idea will fail.  And when you do it, they’ll try and put it down to make themselves feel better. If you listen to “most people”, focus on why they say “you’ll fail”, you’ll never get it done!

Beyond my wildest dreams, I can finally say, it got done!  I am a member and owner of a Fintech App, FinTron, in which you can budget, bank and invest with commission-free trading in over 2,000 stocks and ETFs.  This platform is built for the common consumer.  With a priority of educating each individual to become confident and in control of their finances. 

Check out link for the Fintron app in bio!

🔹 Buy into companies with fractional shares for as little as $10/share.

🔹Fully Automated Repeat Investment Tools for those who need assistance.
 
🔹 Safety features tailored to your investment experience.

🔹A Fintron University, a financial education platform where you can learn basics and invest with free simulation before ever risking a dime.

🔹 5% of all net profits committed to create programs to build financially literacy.

🔹 Banking, Investing and Budgeting reborn with a fully secure 256-bit encrypted data protection. SEC registered. SIPC-insured accounts up to $500,000 and a member of the Financial Industry Regulatory Authority (FINRA).

A Financial app for our generation built by our generation. Check out link for Fintron in bio!

node.text: family for the holiday. Shame on us, we didn’t stick to the plan. We made an adult decision to allow a friend over during the quarantine time bc for a project she was working on she was required to be tested and showed 4 negative tests in a row for her work. On her way home Sunday, her Saturday morning test result came in positive. You just can never be too cautious and careful. There’s no outthinking this god awful virus, lesson learned.  Thoughts and prayers are with all of those who have been impacted by Covid, to those who have endured a challenging 2020, to the healthcare workers putting their lives on the line everyday for others and to those who are family less during the holiday. ❤️
